    "Id": "chassisdef_buccaneer_BCN-6PX_pan",
    "Name": "Buccaneer",
    "Details": "Debuted in 3140 on The Scrapyard Arena and piloted by Robert Driscan, the Pan makes several changes that give it an entirely new look and profile. A small vibroblade styled to resemble a 'Mech-scale parrying dagger replaces the original hatchet, and a collapsible partial wing assembly of Clan design featuring rounded-tip wings has been added to improve movement. These wings boost the already-impressive jump radius provided by the 'Mech's improved jump jets, allowing Pan to clear up to 330 meters in a single bound. Even with Clan-spec components used to save space and mass, this Buccaneer trades a lot of its original firepower away for its mobility. Because of this, Pan carries only three weapons, all of them lasers: two medium re-engineered lasers, able to cut through virtually any armor type, and one Inner Sphere ER medium laser. Double heat sinks and Clan ferro-fibrous armor complete the mix. The Pan's limited firepower means that slugging it out with one's adversary is just not an option for this 'Mech; agility and mobility are the order of the day for this machine.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Rugged</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.07</color></b>",
    "Icon": "uixTxrIcon_buccaneer"
